SWIFT, Appellant, v. SWIFT, Respondent. (Supreme Court, General Term, Third Department. May 26, 1894.) Action by Margaret A. Swift against Charles H. Swift.

Argued before MAYHAM, JJ., and PUTNAM and HERRICK, JJ.

No opinion. Judgment and conviction upon which it is founded, so far as it awards costs, reversed, and set aside, with $10 costs of appeal and printing disbursements.
